# SMTP Configuration for OTP Email Service
# ===========================================

# Gmail SMTP Configuration (recommended for development)


# Alternative: Outlook/Hotmail SMTP
# SMTP_HOST=smtp-mail.outlook.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false

# Alternative: SendGrid SMTP
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=apikey
# SMTP_PASS=your-sendgrid-api-key

# Alternative: Mailgun SMTP
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.mailgun.org
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=your-mailgun-username
# SMTP_PASS=your-mailgun-password

# Email Configuration
SMTP_FROM=no-reply@50brains.com
APP_NAME=50Brains
COMPANY_NAME=50Brains
SUPPORT_EMAIL=support@50brains.com

# Instructions for Gmail Setup:
# =============================
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Gmail account
# 2. Go to Google Account settings -> Security -> App passwords
# 3. Generate an app password for "Mail"
# 4. Use your Gmail address as SMTP_USER
# 5. Use the generated app password as SMTP_PASS

# Instructions for Production:
# ============================
# For production environments, consider using:
# - SendGrid (https://sendgrid.com/)
# - Mailgun (https://www.mailgun.com/)
# - Amazon SES (https://aws.amazon.com/ses/)
# - Postmark (https://postmarkapp.com/)

# Security Notes:
# ===============
# - Never commit actual credentials to version control
# - Use environment-specific .env files
# - Consider using secret management services in production
# - Rotate credentials regularly
# - Monitor email sending quotas and limits